While the in-game events are eye-popping and hint to a future in which game=
s are much more than games, in-game purchases are more economically importa=
nt today.=C2=A0
Most of the $109 billion in virtual marketplace revenue goes not to the pla=
tforms or game developers, but to individuals and small companies that crea=
te digital items for purchase in-game. In games like Roblox and Manticore, =
users create and monetize not just in-game items, but their own games and t=
heir own worlds. In 2020, Roblox expects that its creators will generate ov=
er $250 million [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxVUdGOpCAQ_Bp5w2CLIz74s=
Nm7_Q2D0DNDBsFAu7Pe1x_qw-USQne6U12VKqMJHzHt4xozsS1jmpwdmxuotpMDs6O0jeoUc3m6=
