The definition of a video game is evolving beyond the OED=E2=80=99s: =E2=80=
=9Ca game played by electronically manipulating images produced by a comput=
er program on a television screen or other display screen.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
Increasingly, video games and work will blur, and video game dynamics will =
be an abstraction layer on top of the real world. Just as Ender was able to=
 make decisions without worrying about the details and the Daemon built an =
economy by incentivizing thousands of participants with Darknet credits, I =
think that we will be able to run businesses a layer of abstraction up from=
 the way we run them today. Kind of like playing a game.=C2=A0=C2=A0
What It Takes to Run a Business Today
As more entrepreneurs build more and better software products to help compa=
nies launch, manage, and grow, more of the value chain becomes commoditized=
=2E For example, there are multiple soft=
ware and services companies that hand=
le each piece of the DTC Value Chain.=C2=A0
In Shopify and the Hard Thing About Easy Things [https://email.mg2.substack=
=2Ecom/c/eJxVUEFuhDAMfM3mBgomgXDIoZd-AwV=
ilmghQYnTit83C1KrSrZseWyPZmZD-Azx1EdI=
xHLCODqrmw5UK8XArBa2UVIxl8YlIu7GbZpiRnbkaXOzIRf8dcE5SLbqpQO5iKVbelBC9tYYKyx=
i34iZg20Fe_OMJluHfkaNXxjP4JFteiU60qP9eMBnCR9oCtH5Z53ylMjMr3oOewGOkmkNh1vOyn=
hb0YrVauK7KduVmUKmynDJnAYOnA-gGpBDq-qmVqIHPjiv9tdD8P0J_56zqH9ZC_xazY7bBRStY=
6l79o7OEb2ZNrS3DXQbd6mi80Dt8TttSITxHhZvBCglgbNCZkNx0P_x_ABcfINe], we discus=
sed the idea that the commoditization of the DTC value chain means that it=
=E2=80=99s harder than ever to stand out from the crowd.=C2=A0
More software has another implication that we=E2=80=99ll focus on today: op=
erators are running their businesses at ever-higher levels of abstraction.=
=C2=A0
What does that mean? Just like video games allow players to control their c=
haracters=E2=80=99 moves by pressing some buttons, B2B software lets operat=
ors track and control things that entire teams of employees once did with a=
 few clicks.=C2=A0
But it=E2=80=99s not just ecommerce. Venture capitalist Nikhil Basu Trivedi=
 recently wrote about Business-in-a-Box Platforms [https://email.mg2.substa=
ck.com/c/eJxVUEtuhTAMPM3LDpSE0JpFFt30GigfAxGQoMS04vZNYVFVsmVpRvZ4xhnCOeVLH6=
kQOwvmMXgt3iR0vRqY18oL6IGFMk4ZcTdh05RPZMdpt-AMhRTvDc5lzxbdOQ4chLU9Kuc9B1Rgh=
BLGKSG4t-xXZzSnDxgdavzCfKWIbNML0VFe3cdLftaKltpy2kLGra1Le4WO2mVJR5iuxkTf0ILN=
ilfj0YVS32imlFnQkkvOBwlC9kMHrWhBvUs-hAj7-lJ8n-W_wyzrmMimHOJc6XUxO243UR2Ode5=
nDHSNGI3d0D_m6Ynr9kLXgTrid9mQCPMD1kSUBOglZ1XMp5pb_NP5AQzrf8M] (BiaB), inclu=
ding but not limited to Shopify, that =E2=80=9Cenable new businesses to be =
started, managed, and grown using their products.=E2=80=9D These BiaB compa=
nies all take a set of products someone would need to start a business in a=
 particular vertical, bundle them together, and sell them to aspiring entre=
preneurs. They abstract away the complexity of building a business, and nar=
row the set of choices an entrepreneur needs to make.=C2=A0
For=C2=A0Phyllis Schlafly [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFULuOwyAQ_Jp=
QIp4OLijSpLtvQNhsHGQDFqwv8t8fSYqTVhrtjFazM7NHWEo97V4akqNBdTFYPggjtRpJsCpwow=
2JzT0qQPJxs1gPIPsxbXH2GEv-XDAmNHla_9DXmXGu9ajhcdVh4JNWShovJQxSkbeP80eIkGew8=
Av1LBnIZp-Ie7vI20Xc-0Cmr7jGHUL0tNSlU--9w09t1N0S1O7uSLSCCcZGYbjQozSUU6Ougo0x=
m7ReFEuLoO2YGvp5pXNJpNpccCo15qXL69Mn2D5CT-Q6piNHPB1kP20QvmHxW8_ndzx3sBlebQN=
EqF-yN6CEMVow0s1C6T3lf58_NiN48g(miniseries)]=C2=A0to send her anti-feminist=
 newsletter, she needed to maintain a list of addresses, type up hundreds o=
f copies, stuff and lick envelopes, and send them out through the postal sy=
stem. For me to send you this newsletter, all I have to do is open a new Su=
bstack post (spend 30-50 hours researching and writing) and hit send.=C2=A0
Want to teach people guitar? You no longer need to start a school, rent a s=
pace, or put up flyers all around New York City. Just set up a Teachable ac=
count, record what you know, set it live, and start making money.=C2=A0
Even massive multinational businesses far too complex to run entirely out-o=
f-the-box are now designing products as involved as cars and buildings with=
in the Unity and Unreal engines, avoiding the time, expense, and imprecisio=
n of many rounds of physical prototypes.
Modern software allows business owners and employees to do an increasing pe=
rcentage of the things they need to do through software, and direct an ever=
-larger amount of resources at the click of a button. Take Amazon=E2=80=99s=
=C2=A0Mechanical Turk [https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMtuxCAQ-5rlGPF=
M4cChl_5GRGC6izZABEOj_H1pcqg0kjVjWfbYO4RnqafdS0PSG9QlBstmroWShgQrA9NKk9iW7w=
qQXNws1g5k7-sWvcNY8qWglCvyskIyIYJU4DwFMRBkMLMwijLmZ-PIn8_ieoiQPVj4gXqWDGSzL=
8S9PcTng3-NOY5jStjre_IljZ1Eyymn1HDNuDJCT2zS8oNTE7NO74ek6cmn1teGzl8iUm0uuJYa=
83PQ75dLsF3EiL4MTD1HPBfIbt0g3F_h3cMVEs8dbIajbYAI9T6OVyXXWnFKhlkoo5D87_MLwMN=
w_Q], for example.=C2=A0
Previously, if you wanted people to perform a task, you had to source, hire=
, train, and pay each person separately. Today, you can access thousands of=
 peoples=E2=80=99 labor by typing a few keys. This same dynamic plays out i=
n a more personalized way across platforms like=C2=A0Fiverr [https://email.=
mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUM1uhiAQfJqPo8EVFQ4ceulrGNBViQoGlhrfvlQPTTbZZCaT-RkN=
4RLirc-QiOWEcXCTrjuQTSsUm7SYatlK5tIwR8TDuF1TzMjObHc3GnLBPwrOoWWrnpVQVqCcuSi=
AtYB9DV2nul4qDrbois9g8uTQj6jxB-MdPLJdr0Rn-jRfH_gud11XNbvCxmoMRwGY08CBcwWyhl=
Y1sqorKXrgynl5bB_BjwWqlG0iM25_Iha1D2RDdH4p9LaaA_eHKNmH8o_sHd0DemN3nN5a9A7xp=
KT7RO3xSjsSYXzB0lWAlC1wVsymUBbx_z6_HahxPQ]=C2=A0and=C2=A0Dribbble [https://=
email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFUEuOhSAQPM1jaQBhxAWL2bxrGJBWiQgGmpl4--HpYpJOOt=
2VSn1mg7CmfOkzFSS1QJ680-yLq16KkTgtHFNSEV-mJQMcxgeNuQI5qw1-NuhTvBmUckk2bQUIM=
TgGkvVypANzCzWDEG5YuLPCkY_OZKrzEGfQ8AP5ShFI0BviWV7994u_27jsrbUBujkd7SRec8op=
HbliXI696linxMDp6KM69pegx8q7Um1BM-8fEsk6JrQp-7g2eN_MAeEGmvOp7aNGj9cE0TQZ94T=
Cp4bbI14n6Ai_JQAi5OfZkgqulOSUNDGXWh_xX-cPgLRwzw].=C2=A0=C2=A0
Each of the pieces alone doesn=E2=80=99t seem revolutionary. We=E2=80=99ve =
been able to contract small amounts of peoples=E2=80=99 time for a while. D=
igital prototyping isn=E2=80=99t new. We communicate with humans and bots i=
n the same Slack window all the time. Software and automation are integral =
to modern business and have been for decades.=C2=A0
From inside the day-to-day progress, it=E2=80=99s hard to grasp a paradigm =
shift. But when you zoom out and look at all of the pieces coming together,=
 the possibilities get exciting. We=E2=80=99re getting close to Business-as=
-a-Game.
So what would a Business-as-a-Game Look Like?
To find out what business might look like as a game, how we=E2=80=99re all =
becoming investors, and whether or not this is just a dystopian nightmare=
