46Sn0mTJt-zSDyzXgdUeCFkywSx8XcuxVxzs1PAQbQ1Tr-zawdRZdqbagce-LSbKOCW3KIc5t_H=
41yvIZtN-nltcaA54TRGMX8F9b8Gvk50s8N9CX7AUQIX-bzatBKCUFIw3mU3M0_nP-ABP0iMo" =
style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">recruiting video game=
rs</a>. It even put together an all-Army esports team to compete in <em>Cal=
l of Duty</em>, <em>Fortnite</em>, and <em>League of Legends</em> tournamen=
ts across the country. As war-based Massively Multiplayer Online Games (MMO=
Gs) become more realistic and war is increasingly fought via drones, the sk=
ills required to be good at each are converging.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color=
: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Business=
 has a history of following defense. Many of the once-advanced technologies=
 that underpin the economy today, from the internet to GPS, computers to di=
gital cameras, were first developed for the military before being commercia=
lized by private industry.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Just as <em>Ender&#8217;s Game=
 </em>predicted video games&#8217; growing importance in war way back in 19=
85, Daniel Suarez&#8217;s <em><a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/e=
JxFkE1vhCAQhn-NHA0MuOKBQ5tmj02atmcDMu4SBQxijf31xd1Dk8lM5vPJvIPOeIvpUEtcM9lW=
TL2zil1A8kZ0xCphmWwkcWs_JkSv3axy2pAsm5ndoLOL4bFBKTTkrng7WiNa7JrRSBw1tC03ko3=
AYMCLleTk9HqzDsOACn8wHTEgmdU952Wt-EsF12L7vtfa698Y6iH6UrBLca-UcvnxDi-f5xS_9u=
VItC7cKv72_XWVFVxMnlLJGHEKKFDagWTQdFzWrJaiBdq5IP1UCepvUK-bWbMephNCkgoxm5jOe=
4JOd-1xfjTKr32JfgsuH4WpzYz2KUN-Cvf4Kh8LqoD7OmPOmJ7Foo0AKRugpMBsLAqGf84fpP5_=
uw" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">Daemon</a></em> n=
ovels described a future in which an artificial intelligence runs the econo=
my by controlling humans like video game characters. You should read that o=
ne, too, but here&#8217;s the PacksNotes:&nbsp;</p><blockquote style=3D"bor=
der-left: 4px solid #67bdfc; margin: 1em 0;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; fo=
nt-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0; margin-left: 1em;">Whe=
n video game developer Matthew Sobol dies, he unleashes a computer program,=
 the Daemon, on the world. It infiltrates the computer systems of major cor=
porations and governments, crippling them, while simultaneously coordinatin=
g the actions of Daemon-sympathetic humans on the Darknet, an Augmented Rea=
lity layer that turns the physical world into a video game. By incentivizin=
g humans with points, status, and credits, the Daemon turns civilization in=
to a video game and rebuilds a new economy from the ground up.&nbsp;</p></b=
lockquote><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; m=
argin: 0 0 1em 0;">Today, three trends are converging to make a version of =
Suarez&#8217;s predictions possible:&nbsp;</p><ol style=3D"margin: 1em 0;">=
<li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p=
 style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><=
strong>Video Games are Eating the World.</strong> Video games are worth mor=
e than the film industry already, and games are spawning thriving virtual e=
conomies.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-f=
ormat: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 2=
6px; margin: 0;"><strong>Business-in-a-Box (BiaB). </strong>Software is rep=
lacing more pieces of every industry&#8217;s value chain, and making it eas=
ier to operate businesses at higher levels of abstraction.</p></li><li styl=
e=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong=
>Everyone is an Investor.</strong> As more assets become more investible by=
 more people, we move up another level of abstraction, to the point where m=
ore of our work is a capital allocation game.&nbsp;</p></li></ol><p style=
=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;"=
>Together, these three trends mean that Suarez&#8217;s vision is possible, =
but instead of AI controlling humans like video game characters, humans wil=
l run <strong>Business-as-a-Game (BaaG). </strong>That means:</p><ul style=
=3D"margin: 1em 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special=
-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height:=
 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>Game-like Environment with Real-World Implicatio=
ns.</strong> One digital interface through which an operator or operators c=
an run a business and lead people, like a MMOG.&nbsp;</p></li><li style=3D"=
margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"col=
or: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>High L=
evel of Abstraction. </strong>The business should operate at a high enough =
level of abstraction that goals are understood and important metrics are tr=
ackable and actionable, like numeric attributes, health scores, and points =
in games.&nbsp;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-spe=
cial-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>Persistent Environment, Liquid Resources. </=
strong>Because of clarity around goals and metrics, players should be able =
to join and leave companies on-demand, like Uber drivers with specialized s=
kills, aiding in the quest when most useful.&nbsp;</p></li><li style=3D"mar=
gin: 3.75px 0 3.75px 7.5px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"color:=
 #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0;"><strong>Rewards B=
ased on Skills and Contributions.</strong> People should be able to join co=
mpanies semi-anonymously, via an avatar tied to a confirmed real identity t=
hat is not necessarily visible to the employee (<a href=3D"https://email.mg=
2.substack.com/c/eJxFUMmKhTAQ_BpzlCQuEw85zGV-Q7K0GswiSWce_v0EPQw0NFRR1GIUwp=
7yLa9UkNQCeXVWspmLYRoXYuVomZgEcWXdMkBQzkvMFchVtXdGoUvxUVDKJ3JIMStKLVtmy9Smr=
WawGKu3kdttY2ZuuuazqmodRAMSfiHfKQLx8kC8Sjd8d_ynncnVOO2hj4CflM8GESc55ZQuXDA-=
LYPoWS_GL04XF0U4u5GGnfel6oLKnL1JgWQZE-qUXdwbfR4qgH-Iln5tP9To8F4hqmZl32L4TvH=
kxPsCGeFTPCBCfsHWduRCTJySZmZT2yT--_wBpLxzyQ" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-=
decoration: underline;">Crucible</a> is making this possible). People will =
be hired and rewarded based on trackable contributions instead of tradition=
al credentials.&nbsp;</p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">At the simplest level, BaaG is =
just a shiny new interface on top of existing tools that makes work feel mo=
re fun. One way to think of it is, &#8220;What if developers built business=
